Considering the small amount of fat and sugar in the batter, this was fabulous(also with some changes suggested by others). I added the fresh rosemary and 1 full tablespoon sugar to batter, added lemon juice to cherries and topped it with maybe 2 tsp sugar. It is delicious --addition of lowfat plain yogurt on top is nice too.

Rating: 4
LOVE to eat this dessert and LOVE to make it. It's easy, can be partially prepared ahead of time and it is always a crowd-pleaser. Like others have said, I add quite a bit of lemon zest to the dry ingredients before adding in the butter. I also sprinkle the sugar over the top much more generously than it says in the recipe. It's great with frozen blackberries too!

