Rating: 4
A followup to the review that said there wasn't enough fruit for a 9x9 pan... well, of course not. The recipe calls for a 9 inch ROUND dish. The difference between the area of the round dish (approx. 64 sq. in.) is substantially less than the area of a 9x9 dish (81 sq. in.). Now I feel like a math geek.

Rating: 4
This was a very nice, small dessert that would make a great summer treat for a small family. I used fresh pitted sweet cherries from a local orchard, but used 15 oz. because some of the reviews indicated that 14 oz. was a little light. This was a fine amount, but cherry lovers might add 2-3 oz. more. I also apparently can't read, as I added ALL of the sugar to the whisked mixture (instead of reserving some for the topping). In fact, some reviews indicated that they found the topping bland, so I added even more -- 1.5 Tbsp of sugar -- right into the mix and still topped it with .5 Tbsp of sugar at the end. I also substituted 1/2 cu milk and a generous 3/4 tsp cream of tartar (whisked briskly) into the mix since I did not have any buttermilk. The result? Yummy! Two adults polished off 3/4 of the cobbler in one sitting!

